issue.title: Google-Mobile-Ads-SDK 7.68.0 is broken as bintray is not available
issue.body: ### [REQUIRED] Step 1: Describe your environment * Google Mobile Ads Unity plugin version: 7.68.0 * Platform: iOS * Platform OS version: iOS 14.5 * Any specific devices issue occurs on: Cocoapod install * Mediation ad networks used, and their versions: _____ ### [REQUIRED] Step 2: Describe the problem #### Steps to reproduce: While trying to install Google-Mobile-Ads-SDK 7.68.0, it installs GoogleMobileAdsMediationFacebook 6.2.0.0 as a dependency which fails during `pod install` Not able to reach this URL: [https://google.bintray.com/mobile-ads-adapters-ios/FacebookAdapter/6.2.0.0/FacebookAdapter-6.2.0.0.zip](https://google.bintray.com/mobile-ads-adapters-ios/FacebookAdapter/6.2.0.0/FacebookAdapter-6.2.0.0.zip)

issue.body:
In podFile
pod 'BaiduMapKit','6.3.1'
pod 'Google-Mobile-Ads-SDK','8.8.0'

issue.title: Interstitial ad - GADMobileAds.applicationMuted isn't working as expected
issue.body:
This is can be reproduced by replacing the unit id with `ca-app-pub-3940256099942544/8691691433` which is from
https://developers.google.com/admob/android/test-ads

The ad sound still play out even if `GADMobileAds.sharedInstance().applicationMuted = true` before load Ad

issue.title: IOS 16 devices:  Banners and interstitial ads cannot be displayed
issue.body:
Hello everybody

When my own ios app was upgraded to 16.x, banners and interstitials didn't show up. I downloaded admob's official banner and interstitial code, ran it with xcode and found that the ads could not be displayed (no error), I hope you can come out and discuss, thank you

masos: ventura 13.0.1
xcode: 14.1
ios: 16.1.1 (ipad, iphone14 and so on)
Google Mobile Ads SDK: The latest Version
